Mr. Speaker, whereas the Quebec Charter of Rights and Freedoms guarantees the right of each individual to have and to exercise on an equal basis human rights and freedoms without distinction, discrimination or preference based, in particular, on race, colour, religion or ethnic origin;
Whereas the Sorel area, as well as the rest of the province of Quebec, is intended to be a host territory for any person who wants to settle there;
Whereas the citizens of Richelieu condemn the distribution of hate propaganda and any other form of violence or discrimination based, in particular, on sex, race, colour, religion or ethnic origin;
Whereas the people of the Sorel area, as well as the people of Quebec, long to live in a harmonious society where each and every man and woman has equal opportunities to live, grow and work;
I decry, as federal member of Parliament for Richelieu, along with several organizations in my riding, any racist, discriminatory rally promoting hate and violence to be held in the Sorel area.
